# Billing Rules

## Before touching billing code

Read ALL of:
- `app/api/billing/checkout/route.ts`
- `app/api/billing/webhook/route.ts`
- `lib/stripe.ts`
- `lib/package-plans.ts`
- `lib/plan-entitlements.ts`
- `lib/stripe-price-for-plan.ts`
- `supabase/migrations/202602150004_create_subscriptions_table.sql`
- `supabase/migrations/202602150005_add_stripe_columns.sql`
- `supabase/migrations/202602150006_create_stripe_webhook_events_table.sql`
- `supabase/migrations/202603100002_expand_subscription_statuses.sql`

## Source of truth

Stripe is authoritative. `subscriptions` table is a mirror.
**Never write to `subscriptions` from any route except `app/api/billing/webhook/route.ts`.**

## Webhook idempotency (mandatory)

```
1. lockStripeEvent(event) — INSERT into stripe_webhook_events
   - PG 23505 (duplicate) → return 200 immediately, skip processing
   - PG 42P01 (missing table) → throw (cannot guarantee idempotency)
2. Process event
3. markStripeEventProcessed(event.id)
```

If `stripe_webhook_events` does not exist, refuse to process.

## Plans (lib/package-plans.ts)

| Key | Price | Mode |
|---|---|---|
| `starter` | $299/mo | subscription |
| `professional` | $599/mo | subscription |
| `elite` | $1,299/mo | subscription |
| `single_batch` | $399 | payment |
| `partner_70_30` | $100/mo | subscription |
| `partner_50_50` | $1/mo | subscription |

Price IDs resolved from env vars: `STRIPE_PRICE_ID_STARTER`, `STRIPE_PRICE_ID_PROFESSIONAL`, etc.
Map price ID → plan key via `getPlanKeyForStripePriceId()` in `lib/plan-entitlements.ts`.

## Entitlements (lib/plan-entitlements.ts)

| Plan | Images/mo | Videos/mo |
|---|---|---|
| starter | 45 | 5 |
| professional | 90 | 15 |
| elite | 200 | 35 |
| single_batch | 45 | 0 |
| partner_70_30 | 45 | 5 |
| partner_50_50 | 90 | 15 |

**Always check entitlements server-side.** Never trust client-side plan claims.
Use `getCurrentSubscriptionSummary(admin, userId)` from `lib/request-planner.ts`.

## Subscription status values

Allowed in `subscriptions.status`:
`active`, `trialing`, `past_due`, `canceled`, `expired`, `incomplete`, `needs_review`

Stripe `unpaid` → maps to `past_due` in DB.
`customer.subscription.deleted` event → always `canceled` regardless of Stripe status.

## stripe_customer_id

Stored on `profiles.stripe_customer_id`. Links Supabase user to Stripe customer.
- Set by webhook when `checkout.session.completed` fires
- Required before creating portal session (`/api/billing/portal` creates it if missing)

## Checkout metadata

Plan checkout sets: `source`, `plan`, `creator_id` (service creator), `subscriber_id`, optionally `lead_id`.
Creator subscription sets: `creator_id`, `subscriber_id`.
Admin payment link sets: `source = "admin_pay_link"`, `plan`, `creator_id`, optionally `lead_id`.

## Webhook events handled

- `checkout.session.completed` — provision user, profile, subscription
- `customer.subscription.created/updated/deleted` — sync subscription status
- `invoice.payment_failed` — mark `past_due`, log to `revenue_events`, log to `system_events`

## Billing rules for UI

- Never show Stripe IDs, price IDs, or subscription IDs to customers
- Never use "invoice", "subscription object", "customer portal" in customer-facing copy
- "Payment issue — please update your billing details" not "status: past_due"
- Use `/billing` page for customer self-service (links to Stripe portal)
